Can't we just use /vendor/... everywhere? Can't it follow the symlink?

Patch Set 1:

> Can't we just use /vendor/... everywhere? Can't it follow the
 > symlink?

I'm not sure using /vendor/ will work, hope Andrei can answer this question

Patch Set 1:

> Can't we just use /vendor/... everywhere? Can't it follow the
 > symlink?

It doesn't do that :-( See https://android-review.googlesource.com/c/platform/system/sepolicy/+/340787. Another possibly more elegant solution is using an M4 macro (e.g., https://gerrit.unlegacy-android.org/#/c/Unlegacy-Android/android_device_bn_common/+/10495). It might even be possible to do BOARD_SEPOLICY_M4DEFS += vendor=\(vendor\|system/vendor\)…
